qas.question: What type of region is somerset

answers.text: Somerset is a rural county of rolling hills

qas.question: What are some areas of Somerset county

answers.text: Blackdown Hills, Mendip Hills, Quantock Hills and Exmoor National Park, and large flat expanses of land including the Somerset Levels

qas.question: How far back was the county populated

answers.text: There is evidence of human occupation from Paleolithic times, and of subsequent settlement in the Roman and Anglo-Saxon periods

qas.question: What Kings rise did the county play part in

answers.text: a significant part in the consolidation of power and rise of King Alfred the Great, and later in the English Civil War and the Monmouth Rebellion

qas.question: What is the city of Bath famous for

answers.text: substantial Georgian architecture and is a UNESCO World Heritage Site
